For Salad, in large resealable plastic bag, combine shrimp, 1 teaspoon Olive Oil and 1 teaspoon Lawry's(R) Lemon Pepper; turn to coat. Close bag and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes. Remove shrimp from marinade, discarding marinade. Grill, turning once, until shrimp turn pink. Meanwhile, for dressing, in small bowl with wire whisk, combine remaining 1/3 cup Olive Oil, remaining 1/2 teaspoon Lemon Pepper and vinegar. In large bowl, combine cucumber, onion and tomato. Add bread, basil and shrimp. Toss with dressing and serve immediately.